		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=vamok&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, at level 15, I have pegged my 2 H slash. Now, I am going to train in 1H slash and try to work it up.<br>Around level 30 you can quest for a sword called a ghoulbane. It is a 1HS with procs an undead DD spell (dismiss undead? memory blank...) That adds to the fun of thrashing on your local grave crawlers.<br><br>There is also a 2H piercer called messenger of the queen that could be quite nice if you could get your hands on it. So far as I know 1H and 2H piercing are just PIERCING as far as training goes.<br><br>So your 2HS most likely will be your primary weap, but dont forsake some of the other skills. When you peg a skill for your level, work on the next 1. Wouldn't it be terrible to get an awesome weap at level 52, and find out your skill with it was 0? Ack.<br><br>Hope this helps :-)</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
