		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.06]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kneesmasher&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Greetings,<br><br>As anyone who has followed these boards can attest, I have regularly preached the virtues of keeping ALL your weapon skills up and viable if you have hopes of seeing the high-end game at some time in your EQ career.&nbsp;&nbsp;Verant has finally recognized that they needed to help the SK's and Paladins with weapons and there are now LOTS of nice weapons out there to choose from for the post-50 crowd in all the different skill areas. Here's a list of just a very few:<br><br>1-hs: Emerald Bastard Sword of Purity<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6119" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6119</a><br><br>2-hs: Ethereal Bladed Naginata (Quest Item)<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6453" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6453</a><br><br>1-hb: Club of the Ice Ocean<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4003" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=4003</a><br><br>2-hb: Rocksmasher<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5901" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5901</a><br><br>2-hb: Shovel of the Harvest<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6441" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6441</a><br><br>2-hp: Narandi's Lance<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6249" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6249</a><br><br>The problem with NOT practicing your skills all along comes when you are level 50+ and you decide to practice some skill, like 2-hb, that you have let languish all the way through your levels.  Watch what happens to your ATTACK ability when you switch weapons! It drops to nothing! People then get discouraged because they can't hit anything and can't do damage, so they switch back to what they have always used: 1-hs or 2-hs.  If you practice these skills all along, as you move up in level, it's MUCH easier.<br><br>I am speaking from experience. I NEVER practiced 2-hb coming up through the ranks. But I recently got the benefit of watching a friend use the AWESOME 2-hb weapon: Rocksmasher. OMG!! It was AMAZING! Hits were common place for well over 200 pts.  It comes with Haste.  The weapon has it all. I immediately began working my skill and it has been a long slow process to try and get it above 200, let alone maxed at 221 for my level.<br><br>So grab that strange weapon that you never use, and get busy. The time to start is NOW!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10212406451013&num=3&post=1&mid=10212406451013><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 al